definition.value: An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of golgi alpha-mannosidase II (mannosyl-oligosaccharide 1,3-1,6-alpha-mannosidase, EC 3.2.1.114), a key enzyme target in the development of anti-cancer therapies.
An agonist that binds to and activates liver receptor homologue-1 (LRH-1).
Substances which are added to food in order to prevent decomposition by microbial growth or by undesirable chemical changes.
A food preservative which prevents decomposition of food by preventing the growth of fungi or bacteria.
A compound that inhibits the action of gamma-aminobutyric acid.
Any substance which is used to neutralise stomach acidity.
An agonist that binds to and activates erythropeotin receptors.
An agonist that binds to and activates prostaglandin receptors.
A membrane transport modulator that restores the chloride ion transport ability of defective cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) genes.
An antagonist that interferes with the action of smoothened (SMO) receptor
A tyrosine kinase inhibitor that specifically blocks the action of Janus kinase.
Any compound which can be used to treat or alleviate the symptoms of dyskinesia.
Any compound that improves mental functions such as cognition, memory, intelligence, motivation, attention, and concentration.
Any compound used for the treatment of eye conditions or eye diseases.
Any compound which inhibits the postganglionic functioning of the sympathetic nervous system (SNS).
Any compound used to suppress premature labour and immature birth by suppressing uterine contractions.
An agonist that binds to and activates cannabinoid receptors.
Any compound that has anti-inflammatory effects.
A chemosterilant intended to sterilize insects.

A ryanodine receptor modulator which activates the receptor. Ryanodine receptors (RyRs) act as selective ion channels, modulating the release of calcium. Activating the receptors causes the release of calcium, so depleting internal calcium and ultimately preventing further muscle contraction.
A reagent used in the determination of the concentration of a coloured chemical element or chemical compound in solution.
In NMR spectroscopy a reagent added to a solution to induce chemical shifts and thus simplify complex spectra.
Any compound that inhibits the growth of new blood vessels from pre-existing vessels.
It is not clear to me how this differs from angiogenesis inhibitor -- cjm
An enzyme inhibitor which inhibits the action of microbial collagenase (EC 3.4.24.3, also formerly EC 3.4.4.19 and EC 3.4.99.5)
An inhibitor that interferes with the process of gap junctional intercellular communication.
An agonist that selectively binds to and activates a retinoic acid receptor.
An antogonist that interferes with the action of activator protein 1 (AP-1).
A provitamin that can be converted into vitamin A by enzymes from animal tissues.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of glucosylceramidase (EC 3.2.1.45).
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of sucrose alpha-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.48).
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of sucrose oligo-1,6-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.10).
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of alpha-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.20).
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of geranylgeranyltransferase type I (EC 2.5.1.59).
An inhibitor of HIV-1 integrase, an enzyme required for the integration of the genetic material of the retrovirus into the DNA of the infected cells.

A protein kinase inhibitor of mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR), a protein that regulates cell growth, cell proliferation, cell motility, cell survival, protein synthesis and transcription. They are used to prevent transplant rejection and in treatment of cancer.
Any substance that inhibits the process of apoptosis (programmed cell death) in multi-celled organisms.
Any substance that induces the process of apoptosis (programmed cell death) in multi-celled organisms.
A compound which causes a reduction in the levels of glutathione in cells.
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of dihydroorotate dehydrogenase (EC 1.3.3.1).
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the synthesis of pyrimidine.
An agonist that selectively binds to and activates guanylate cyclase 2C receptors.
An antagonist at the bradykinin receptor.
An antagonist at the P2Y12 receptor
An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of coagulation factor Xa (EC 3.4.21.6)
A peptidase inhibitor that specifically inhibits dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (EC 3.4.14.5)
A phosphodiesterase inhibitor that specifically blocks the action of  phosphodiesterase IV.
A hormone agonist that binds to and activates progesterone receptors.
An enzyme inhibitor that inhibits the action of acetyl-CoA carboxylase (EC 6.4.1.2).
